Looking at the code, I need to analyze the buggy `injectMockCandidate` method and determine which test cases expose the bug.

The buggy method:
```java
private void injectMockCandidate(Class<?> awaitingInjectionClazz, Set<Object> mocks, Object fieldInstance) {
    for(Field field : orderedInstanceFieldsFrom(awaitingInjectionClazz)) {
        mockCandidateFilter.filterCandidate(mocks, field, fieldInstance).thenInject();
    }
}
```

The issue is that this method only processes fields from `awaitingInjectionClazz` itself, but it doesn't handle inherited fields from parent classes. This means if a class has a parent class with fields that need mock injection, those parent fields will be ignored.

Analyzing the test cases:

1. Tests that involve class hierarchies or inheritance would be affected
2. The key test case is `shouldInjectMocksForClassHierarchyIfAnnotated` which explicitly tests inheritance
3. `injectMocksShouldInjectMocksFromTestSuperClasses` also tests parent class injection
4. Any test that involves a class hierarchy where parent fields need injection

The fix needs to traverse the entire class hierarchy, not just the immediate class.

```java
private void injectMockCandidate(Class<?> awaitingInjectionClazz, Set<Object> mocks, Object fieldInstance) {
    for(Class<?> classContext = awaitingInjectionClazz; classContext != Object.class; classContext = classContext.getSuperclass()) {
        for(Field field : orderedInstanceFieldsFrom(classContext)) {
            mockCandidateFilter.filterCandidate(mocks, field, fieldInstance).thenInject();
        }
    }
}
```

Now identifying which tests trigger this bug - tests that rely on injection into parent class fields:

{
  "trigger_method": [
    "org.mockitousage.annotation.MockInjectionTest::shouldInjectMocksForClassHierarchyIfAnnotated",
    "org.mockitousage.bugs.ParentTestMockInjectionTest::injectMocksShouldInjectMocksFromTestSuperClasses"
  ],
  "fixed_code": [
    "private void injectMockCandidate(Class<?> awaitingInjectionClazz, Set<Object> mocks, Object fieldInstance) {\n    for(Class<?> classContext = awaitingInjectionClazz; classContext != Object.class; classContext = classContext.getSuperclass()) {\n        for(Field field : orderedInstanceFieldsFrom(classContext)) {\n            mockCandidateFilter.filterCandidate(mocks, field, fieldInstance).thenInject();\n        }\n    }\n}"
  ]
}
